1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:04,160
Before we finally start working on the implementation of our model,

2

00:00:04,160  -->  00:00:06,940
let's briefly refresh an important technique

3

00:00:06,940  -->  00:00:09,900
we will be using throughout our implementation,

4

00:00:09,900  -->  00:00:12,790
which is called the dropout layer.

5

00:00:12,790  -->  00:00:16,425
If we have a feedforward neural network,

6

00:00:16,425  -->  00:00:22,965
each output from a previous layer goes to all neurons of the next layer.

7

00:00:22,965  -->  00:00:28,725
However, if we introduce a dropout layer in our neural network,

8

00:00:28,725  -->  00:00:32,390
then during training, a certain percentage of

9

00:00:32,390  -->  00:00:38,070
randomly selected inputs will be set to zero on each training iteration.

10

00:00:38,070  -->  00:00:43,570
The list of disabled inputs will change from one iteration to the other.

11

00:00:43,570  -->  00:00:46,970
This allows to ensure that our model does not

12

00:00:46,970  -->  00:00:51,010
learn to depend heavily on any particular input feature.

13

00:00:51,010  -->  00:00:54,350
This in turn helps the model to generalize better,

14

00:00:54,350  -->  00:00:57,675
making it less likely to overfit.

15

00:00:57,675  -->  00:01:02,720
Notice that the dropout layer is only enabled during training.

16

00:01:02,720  -->  00:01:06,020
But when we are using the model to generate text,

17

00:01:06,020  -->  00:01:08,680
the dropout layer will be disabled.

18

00:01:08,680  -->  00:01:12,300
We won't need to implement the dropout layer ourselves since

19

00:01:12,300  -->  00:01:17,510
it's already implemented by the dropout type in PyTorch.
